<div class="description">
    <h3>Description</h3>

    <div class="body">
        <p>The current __construct method looks like this:</p>

<pre class="highlight"><code>
 public function __construct($server, $httpClient = null, $introspector = null)
 {
     if ($httpClient === null) {
         $this-&gt;_httpClient = new Zend_Http_Client();
     }
 
     if ($introspector === null) {
         $this-&gt;_introspector = new Zend_XmlRpc_Client_ServerIntrospection($this);
     }
   
     $this-&gt;_serverAddress = $server;
}
</code></pre>

<p>It would make sense if when I pass Zend_Http_Client to the __construct of Zend_Xmlrpc_Client, that the object is used. I know that there is a setHttpClient() method (aka the workaround), which is why I marked this as an improvement and not a bug.</p>

